Holotype male (Fig. 11): Length to apex of hemelytron ca 3.40 mm (wing separated from body), length to base of cuneus 2.33 mm (wing separated from 
body
), width across hemelytra 1.12 mm. Head: Length 0.43 mm, width across eyes 0.64 mm, interocular width 0.32 mm. Labium: Length 1.12 mm. Antenna: Segment I length 0.32 mm, II 1.04 mm, III 0.64 mm, IV ca 0.51 mm (curled and in glue). Pronotum: Length 0.42 mm, basal width 0.82 mm.

The holotype was taken on Oryza sp. (
Poaceae
).
